reviewText: This is an excellent discussion about President Obama's leadership issues. Charlie Rose interviews Drew Westin, a professor of psychology at Emory University who wrote an article in last week's NY Times Magazine entitled "What Happened to Obama," Jonathan Chait of the New Republic who wrote a response to it, and Fareed Zakaria of Time Magazine and GPS on CNN who wrote an follow-up article discussing both of the prior articles. It is a very thoughtful discussion of divergent viewpoints.
